#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:4 4f2946654f23493f9d61f77810ac5ef6
msgid "Userguides - How To 🙋‍♂️"
msgstr "Руководства пользователя — Как это сделать 🙋‍♂️"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:9 e91a1e90c67343df8c8d41e1a1ba9468
msgid "How to log in using OAuth2"
msgstr "Как войти через OAuth2"

#: ../../source/userguides/oauth2_setup.rst:1 cc6511bbfbee4d98be34b656da6b5668
msgid "**1. Select the** ``Use OAuth2`` **option in the login window**"
msgstr "**1. Выберите опцию** ``Использовать OAuth2`` **в окне входа**"

#: 7d58536f1449474cbf0ed21bc8c8ea09
msgid "OAuth login window"
msgstr "Окно входа OAuth"

#: ../../source/userguides/oauth2_setup.rst:11 52e6942a7ddf4bf39747ba15b4e10bed
msgid "**2. Set the master password**"
msgstr "**2. Установите мастер-пароль**"

#: ../../source/userguides/oauth2_setup.rst:13 48051919e4e14a489c5090658d32871e
msgid ""
"You will be prompted to set a new `master authentication password "
"<https://docs.qgis.org/3.28/en/docs/user_manual/auth_system/auth_overview.html"
"#master-password>`_ - qgis feature to ensure the security of sensitive "
"information storage."
msgstr ""
"Вам будет предложено установить новый `аутентификационный мастер-пароль "
"<https://docs.qgis.org/3.28/en/docs/user_manual/auth_system/auth_overview.html"
"#master-password>`_ - функция qgis, которая обеспечивает безопасность "
"хранения конфиденциальной информации."

#: ../../source/userguides/oauth2_setup.rst:22 2f469115b05640aaafb139999de1b612
msgid "**3. Click** ``Log in`` **button**"
msgstr "**3. Нажмите** ``Войти``"

#: ../../source/userguides/oauth2_setup.rst:24 8e7b6ad5c3d94c7fb367d35ddad7de0a
msgid ""
"You will receive the following message, **restart** QGIS before the next "
"steps."
msgstr ""
"Вы получите следующее сообщение, **перезапустите** QGIS перед выполнением"
" следующих шагов."

#: ../../source/userguides/oauth2_setup.rst:33 16e823e961494c6081ac56dc37e55bbb
msgid "**4. After restarting QGIS, click** ``Log in``"
msgstr "**4. После перезапуска QGIS, нажмите** ``Войти``"

#: ../../source/userguides/oauth2_setup.rst:35 4de32001bd3e4d37b1f3ec664ebbffcd
msgid ""
"You will be redirected to the browser to log in/register in the mapflow "
"system:"
msgstr ""
"Вы будете перенаправлены в браузер для входа в систему/регистрации в "
"системе mapflow:"

#: ../../source/userguides/oauth2_setup.rst:44 e212a3c24f7b4d6b960d21eccef4a312
msgid ""
"After successfully logging in, you will receive a message about the "
"successful verification of QGIS OAuth2:"
msgstr ""
"После успешного входа в систему вы получите сообщение об успешной "
"проверке QGIS OAuth2:"

#: ../../source/userguides/oauth2_setup.rst:53 1f3fe84bf7a74235abb8057f110f5c13
msgid "You can close this page"
msgstr "Можете закрыть эту страницу"

#: ../../source/userguides/oauth2_setup.rst:55 132199317abc4a05819b96e7ce3239bb
msgid "**5. Go back to QGIS**"
msgstr "**5. Вернитесь в QGIS**"

#: ../../source/userguides/oauth2_setup.rst:57 00d281bebd854a199e1246b7a215ad2b
msgid "OAuth login completed!"
msgstr "Входе через OAuth завершен!"

#: ../../source/userguides/oauth2_setup.rst:60 0adef55429b64486a2e6d7f93fde0244
msgid ""
"If you have problems with authorization, you can delete the current "
"authentication config by going to ``Settings -> Options -> "
"Authentication``, select the config and remove it:"
msgstr ""
"Если у вас возникли серьезные проблемы с авторизацией, вы можете удалить "
"конфигурацию аутентификации, перейдя в ``Настройки -> Параметры -> "
"Аутентификация``, выберите конфигурацию и удалите ее:"

#: ../../source/userguides/qgis_plugin.rst:2 abecbe85acc2433d94d27a85bda76079
msgid "How to use the Mapflow <> QGIS plugin"
msgstr "Как пользоваться плагином Mapflow <> QGIS"

#: ../../source/userguides/qgis_plugin.rst:4 2b08eac69dae4b20be3de0e1a2d88231
msgid "**Object mapping in remote sensing images using Mapflow plugin for QGIS**"
msgstr "**Картографирование объектов на снимках ДЗЗ с помощью плагина Mapflow для QGIS**"

#: ../../source/userguides/qgis_plugin.rst:6 f23e6c63a417445ab28fd55fd239666f
msgid ""
"Interpretation and subsequent digitization of satellite imagery is a "
"rather laborious process. The use of AI-based image recognition "
"technologies leads to a reduction in labor costs and an increase in data "
"processing speed."
msgstr ""
"Дешифрирование и последующая оцифровка растровых изображений – довольно "
"трудоемкий процесс. Использование технологий распознавания образов с "
"помощью искусственного интеллекта ведет к снижению трудозатрат и "
"повышению скорости обработки данных."

#: ../../source/userguides/qgis_plugin.rst:8 4c7db13608d24543ba3e809b65a4e761
msgid ""
"In the QGIS, the process of detecting objects of various types can be "
"automated using the Mapflow plugin. To accomplish this, you can follow "
"the steps described below."
msgstr ""
"В геоинформационной системе QGIS процесс оцифровки объектов различного "
"вида может быть автоматизирован с помощью плагина Mapflow. Для этого "
"необходимо осуществить нижеописанные шаги."

#: ../../source/userguides/qgis_plugin.rst:10 25febb92c66b4235920a0975687491d0
msgid "**1. Installation of Mapflow plugin and logging in**"
msgstr "**1. Установка плагина Mapflow для QGIS и авторизация**"

#: ../../source/userguides/qgis_plugin.rst:12 4e592ef8c1934751b26d3a455fc06846
msgid ""
"First of all, you have to install the plugin in QGIS. To do this, go to "
"the tab called Plugins -> Manage and Install Plugins, find Mapflow using "
"the search bar and click Install Plugin."
msgstr ""
"Прежде всего необходимо установить плагин в QGIS. Для этого в главном "
"окне программы следует перейти на вкладку Plugins -> Manage and Install "
"Plugins, найти Mapflow с помощью поисковой строки и нажать Install "
"Plugin."

#: ../../source/userguides/qgis_plugin.rst:21 70b038b1c5554c1795e76e4fac855340
msgid ""
"After installation, the plugin icon will appear in the toolbar: "
"|plugin_icon|. Clicking on it will open the authorization window, in "
"which you need to click on \"Get token\"."
msgstr ""
"После установки иконка плагина появится в панели инструментов: "
"|plugin_icon|. Нажав на неё, откроем окно авторизации, в котором "
"необходимо кликнуть на «Get token»."

#: ../../source/userguides/qgis_plugin.rst:23 1ee6c628d62840ffab436c7218e397a4
#: 94ebae653f9f460f9d2dd2e5bc471e28
msgid "plugin_icon"
msgstr "plugin_icon"

#: ../../source/userguides/qgis_plugin.rst:33 8bf15fb4fec24aea92dedf703d2696f1
msgid ""
"A window will open in which you have to quickly and for free register on "
"`Mapflow.ai <https://app.mapflow.ai/>`_. After that, by clicking on the "
"user, you need to go to Settings and select the API tab."
msgstr ""
"Откроется окно, в котором необходимо осуществить быструю и бесплатную "
"регистрацию на `Mapflow.ai <https://app.mapflow.ai/>`_. После чего, нажав"
" на пользователя необходимо перейти в Настройки и выбрать вкладку API."

#: ../../source/userguides/qgis_plugin.rst:42 775fa524c3b3402196c1551e8a7759b1
msgid ""
"By clicking on the \"Reset api token\" button, you will get access to the"
" authorization key, which must be copied and saved, as well as pasted "
"into the authorization window in QGIS. After that - click \"Log in\"."
msgstr ""
"Нажав на кнопку «Сбросить api токен», мы получим доступ к ключу для "
"авторизации, который необходимо скопировать и сохранить, а также вставить"
" в окно авторизации в QGIS и нажать «Log in»."

#: ../../source/userguides/qgis_plugin.rst:44 01802f67f5754635b21934f33f5c4c1e
msgid ""
"Another way to log in to the plugin is using Oauth2. By checking the "
"appropriate option in the authorization window, you will need to set a "
"master password."
msgstr ""
"Иной способ авторизации в плагине – с использованием Oauth2. Отметив в "
"окне авторизации соответствующую опцию галочкой, необходимо будет "
"установить мастер-пароль."

#: ../../source/userguides/qgis_plugin.rst:53 1957c3379be7488f8ade9c0fb3d4a4b7
msgid ""
"Then, following the instructions, restart QGIS and click \"Log in\" "
"again. This will redirect you to the browser, where the Mapflow "
"authorization window will open. After successful login or registration, a"
" page will open notifying you of this."
msgstr ""
"Затем, следуя инструкциям, перезапустить QGIS и снова нажать «Log in». "
"Это перенаправит Вас в браузер, где откроется окно авторизации в Mapflow."
" После успешного входа или регистрации откроется страница, уведомляющая "
"об этом."

#: ../../source/userguides/qgis_plugin.rst:62 2af35a3bbac1439d8ff328a52b78ad6d
msgid ""
"And in QGIS the main tab of the plugin will open, so you can proceed to "
"the next steps."
msgstr ""
"В QGIS откроется главное окно плагина – можно переходить к выполнению "
"дальнейших шагов."

#: ../../source/userguides/qgis_plugin.rst:64 cc9588c5f83549c7b34eb942aa5a5744
msgid "**2. Object recognition using default data provider**"
msgstr "**2. Распознавание объектов с помощью провайдера данных по умолчанию**"

#: ../../source/userguides/qgis_plugin.rst:66 fe06be6a5a8c452885755daa2cefe6cc
msgid ""
"In order to start processing, first you must specify its name. Next, "
"choose the area of interest by drawing it on the map / loading from a "
"vector file / taking the extent of the map."
msgstr ""
"Для того, чтобы запустить обработку, прежде всего необходимо указать её "
"название. Далее – выбрать территорию интереса, нарисовав ее на карте / "
"подгрузив векторный слой с границами / взяв экстент карты."

#: ../../source/userguides/qgis_plugin.rst:75 e11c613bfab042d9b7dc37eb99c4afc0
msgid ""
"In the upper-left corner of the main QGIS window in the Browser panel, "
"you can open the OpenStreetMap basemap and navigate around the map to "
"identify the area of interest."
msgstr ""
"В левом верхнем углу в окне QGIS на панели «Browser» можно открыть "
"подложку OpenStreetMap и сориентироваться по карте, чтобы обозначить "
"интересующую территорию."

#: ../../source/userguides/qgis_plugin.rst:84 1a2b3d05fdd442c082ceed7691e7a943
msgid ""
"Let’s leave the remaining parameters as default: Mapbox data provider and"
" a model for buildings classification. Then click \"Start processing\". A"
" new row will appear in the processing table. Upon completion of "
"processing (Progress – 100%), after some time, you can load the result to"
" the map by clicking on \"View results\" (or double-clicking on the row)."
" The raster layer and the identified objects will be displayed on the "
"map: buildings are automatically classified by their type (where red is "
"residential and purple is commercial)."
msgstr ""
"В окне плагина остальные параметры оставим дефолтными: в качестве "
"провайдера данных – подложка с данными ДЗЗ от Mapbox, модель – для "
"определения зданий. И нажмем «Start processing». В таблице обработок "
"появится новая строка. По завершении обработки (Progress – 100%) спустя "
"некоторое время можно подгрузить результат на карту, нажав на «View "
"results» (или двойным кликом по строке). На карте отобразится растр и "
"выделенные по нему объекты: здания, автоматически классифицированные по "
"типу (где красный – residential, фиолетовый - commercial)."

#: ../../source/userguides/qgis_plugin.rst:94 b6ad5af43e5a47d68d60b119e4db3884
msgid ""
"The resulting vector objects can be saved in GeoJSON format (by clicking "
"on the additional options next to View results) and then used for "
"mapping, analysis, or filled with additional attribute information."
msgstr ""
"Полученные векторные объекты можно сохранить в формате GeoJSON (нажав на "
"дополнительные опции рядом с View results) и далее использовать для "
"картографирования, анализа или наполнять дополнительной атрибутивной "
"информацией."

#: ../../source/userguides/qgis_plugin.rst:103 053ab0c4623a46cf9990e90823a5b492
msgid "**3. Object recognition using your own imagery**"
msgstr "**3. Распознавание объектов по собственным изображениям**"

#: ../../source/userguides/qgis_plugin.rst:105 9f54f2730c4c466d9a7fbc3d43e6d3b3
msgid ""
"Previously, we looked at one of the simplest scenarios for working with "
"the Mapflow plugin. However, its functionality is not limited to a single"
" data provider. In addition to the default providers, you can use the "
"search in the imagery catalog or process your own images. After adding "
"the image you are interested in to QGIS as a raster layer, you can select"
" it in the \"Data source\" field and run processing. The result can look "
"like this: the boundaries of trees of different heights, identified in "
"your image."
msgstr ""
"Выше рассмотрен один из наиболее простых сценариев работы с плагином "
"Mapflow. Однако его функционал не ограничивается одним провайдером "
"данных. Помимо дефолтных подложек, можно воспользоваться поиском по "
"каталогу спутниковых снимков или использовать собственные изображения. "
"Подгрузив в QGIS интересующее нас изображение, можем выбрать его в поле "
"«Data source» и запустить по нему обработку. Результат: границы лесов "
"разных категорий, дифференцированных по высоте."

#: ../../source/userguides/qgis_plugin.rst:115 b4ffb0db6b334232bc390d812aaed1c0
msgid ""
"In this quick tutorial, we looked at the main options for detecting "
"objects in remote sensing images with the help of the Mapflow plugin for "
"QGIS. In addition to buildings and forest vegetation, there are models "
"for recognizing roads or construction sites. A more extensive overview of"
" the plugin's capabilities, as well as various options for data sources, "
"are discussed in the documentation for :ref:`Mapflow <> QGIS`."
msgstr ""
"Так, были рассмотрены основные возможности автоматизации оцифровки "
"объектов различных категорий по растровым изображениям с помощью плагина "
"Mapflow для QGIS. Помимо зданий и лесной растительности, существуют "
"модели для распознавания дорог или участков строительства. Более обширный"
" обзор возможностей плагина, а также различные варианты источников данных"
" рассмотрены в документации :ref:`Mapflow <> QGIS`."

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:57 00b90dd3773c4a85b1e9bfc6932cebf9
msgid "How to process your own UAV images with Mapflow"
msgstr "Как обрабатывать собственные снимки БПЛА с помощью Mapflow"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:59 11f9965d3a9a4ca9aea6a6c6a8c002b0
msgid ""
"Unmanned aerial vehicles – UAVs or, more commonly, drones – have become a"
" deeply integrated part of the geomatic industry over the last ten years."
" This is owing to their increasing usability, falling hardware costs, and"
" easing government regulations. Yet, as more data is available with UAV "
"surveys, more data need to be processed operatively. To process your UAV "
"data you might be looking for some cloud or desktop software to create a "
"mosaic or orthophoto.  Do you know that you can easily publish your data "
"with Openaerialmap and analyze (say detect and calculate some objects and"
" calculate their areas) with Mapflow QGIS or Mapflow Web?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:62 47a8011954eb4c219423ffee7e83a1d7
msgid ""
"Let’s take the “UAV buildings” :doc:`buildings_aerial_imagery_model` "
"model that extracts the detailed building outlines (the recommended image"
" resolution is 10 cm)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:65 24e5af9df3f7437d87a39a86c687ca7f
msgid "Upload images to Mapflow Web"
msgstr "Загрузка изображений в Mapflow Web"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:67 c5a4b4490ba9405894b807c3ba046609
msgid ""
"Select raster source – you can either use Custom URL (see below how to "
"publish your image with Openaerialmap and get the TMS link) or upload "
"your image as GeoTIFF."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:78 d9a006032cf349a2949e764bde22e7d6
msgid ""
"*Currently, a preview of the uploaded image is not possible after loading"
" the image, you will preview only the area of its extent.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:80 f1c1bf1f5e564009bb1b47ef478b51d8
msgid ""
"2. Define the processing Area. The processing area (AOI) must be located "
"within the area of the image extent, otherwise, the area will be cut off "
"by the extent boundaries. The processing area size is calculated by the "
"intersection of the image extent and the AOI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:85 145816f143b14c98b2487ff81b92586f
msgid ""
"Image upload requirements: The file size must be less than 1 Gb. Both "
"sides image dimmesions must not exceed 30.000x30.000"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:88 bfa47946be6746f7b8f9631ac87220b8
msgid ""
"The image must be georeferenced and the CRS must be one of: * WGS84 "
"(EPSG: 4326) * Web mercator (EPSG: 3857) * UTM (any zone)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:93 80440b8698974261842c6bfd3586bcdf
msgid ""
"If your image doesn’t meet the parameters, we suggest using Mapflow API /"
" QGIS plugin which has more capabilities. Mapflow supports RGB imagery "
"and also processes single-band (panchromatic) imagery, but the AI models "
"are not tuned for such kind of data, so the quality of the result may be "
"worse than expected."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:98 f2d1430b74fe4cc6a86bd48e59691036
msgid "Upload images with Mapflow – QGIS"
msgstr "Загрузка изображений через Mapflow – QGIS"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:100 166522bad45545a4928a57eae75e18c8
msgid ""
"You can upload your own GeoTIFF (up to 1 GB, max. 30000x30000 px. by "
"default). All raster layers loaded in your QGIS (1) are visible in the "
"drop-down list (2) and can be selected for upload."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:110 fe3b0c2e74114c01be113832f609a3d5
msgid ""
"Please, consider the requirements for :ref:`AI Models <Model "
"requirements>` when uploading your own images. Contact us if you have "
"difficulties to handle a large dataset or your file size exceeds our "
"limits."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:115 012f636bfd9845da9be4ce44260acef2
msgid "How to use external data providers in Mapflow"
msgstr "Как использовать внешние провайдеры данных в Mapflow"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:120 64976498decf4c2bace866d0aecf4640
msgid "Use Openaerialmap as an imagery publication and access service"
msgstr "Использование OpenAerialMap как сервиса публикации и доступа к снимкам"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:122 c09738cfedbc458eb03b7d9c1be2f108
msgid ""
"`OpenAerialMap <https://openaerialmap.org/>`_ is an open collection of "
"UAV imagery data, crowdsourced by users. The project is supported by a "
"consortium of companies developing open source software and services for "
"working with spatial data. As soon as your aerial image is published on "
"OpenAerialMap it's presented on the public map and can be fetched using "
"TMS/WMTS protocols."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:125 aacf939185db42049d7059f5401332c6
msgid "Select the image and copy link to TMS to connect it to Mapflow Custom URL."
msgstr "Выберите снимок и скопируйте ссылку TMS для подключения к Mapflow через пользовательский URL."

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst de3416fc5a2546128d1f957b5d764888
msgid "Search for imagery in OpenAerialMap"
msgstr "Поиск снимков в OpenAerialMap"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:133 029f786de8f24c10b975acb498389516
msgid ""
"Copy link to TMS and paste it into the “Custom imagery URL” in your new "
"Mapflow processing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:134 49fd60ba5adf468b8709d6acc0261e86
msgid ""
"Check if you see the image on the map, go through the next steps (AI "
"model, processing params) to and start the processing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:142 b2e81616b8394e7489f0670fb1a514c3
msgid "..note::"
msgstr "..note::"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:138 89dfc7ab12144d2c9b46c98ad3c3dee3
msgid ""
"Your can use this service to publish your own UAV data (note that it will"
" become publicly accessible). As soon as your aerial image is published "
"on Openaerialmap it’s displayed on the public map and can be connected "
"using TMS/WMTS or downloaded as GeoTIFF file. Both ways are OK to work "
"with Mapflow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:147 795d8ca7aca74a6ba37ba6930f9448de
msgid "Use Nearmap as an imagery provider"
msgstr "Использование Nearmap в качестве провайдера снимков"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:149 4e802a255c114f7382048c6ee0966995
msgid ""
"`Nearmap <https://nearmap.com>`_ provides access to its Vertical and "
"Panorama Imagery via a Tile API. If you have a subscription to their "
"service you can use it easily with Mapflow Custom URL."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:151 de9ed146a4e84cf782fa74bcb254392f
msgid "URL format:"
msgstr "Формат URL:"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:153 23db0f13670946f189eb48649580e4b1
msgid "``https://api.nearmap.com/tiles/v3/{tileResourceType}/{z}/{x}/{y}.{format}?apikey={YOUR_API_KEY}``"
msgstr "``https://api.nearmap.com/tiles/v3/{tileResourceType}/{z}/{x}/{y}.{format}?apikey={YOUR_API_KEY}``"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:155 d4549699251e4d3e8a6f7bda4069a19b
msgid ""
"Find more in the Nearmap `API documentation "
"<https://help.nearmap.com/kb/articles/84-tile-api>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:162 3f01b31234fe4b50b132d791997a52a7
msgid "Nearmap imagery preview in Mapflow W"
msgstr "Предварительный просмотр снимков Nearmap в Mapflow Web"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:168 4675e07073b14d44bf2b0c23f5d319c5
msgid "Use NAIP as an imagery provider"
msgstr "Использование NAIP в качестве провайдера снимков"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:171 73edcb4f31c84f98b33147b0dbb44c56
msgid ""
"NAIP (National Agriculture Imagery Program) provides public access to "
"aerial imagery for the US territory. The data is available as a set of "
"tiles via TMS protocol. It's effectively public-domain data so you are "
"free to use, redistribute, incorporate into commercial or open-source "
"projects, or mix with other data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:173 7d578de573394fb890703eb9f8dbfbfd
msgid ""
"To use NAIP data with Mapflow Custom URL, you can use the following TMS "
"URL template:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:175 569a90015bd44d80b2cbd408e7e0021e
msgid "``https://gis.apfo.usda.gov/arcgis/rest/services/NAIP/USDA_CONUS_PRIME/ImageServer/tile/{z}/{y}/{x}?blankTile=false``"
msgstr "``https://gis.apfo.usda.gov/arcgis/rest/services/NAIP/USDA_CONUS_PRIME/ImageServer/tile/{z}/{y}/{x}?blankTile=false``"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:183
#: 5b9b6dab03134bbb8069490bb0548e01 8783a20a16e34182adb780bf40c6f6f5
msgid "Multi-modal analysis using NAIP imagery"
msgstr "Мультимодальный анализ на основе снимков NAIP"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:188 80e9afb0171342e38d3257ae58582ecc
msgid "How to optimize large image files"
msgstr "Как оптимизировать большие файлы изображений"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:191 8d68939188324724956f393d565acdc5
msgid "Preparing and optimizing the large size images"
msgstr "Подготовка и оптимизация изображений большого размера"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:193 ed168342a51244fe9c1c66ff753c2dd1
msgid ""
"Here are few tips on how to prepare and optimize your data and reduce the"
" image size to upload it faster and not to exceed the Mapflow upload "
"limit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:195 35f3bbe86e474586b60b1cfb26fc5342
msgid ""
"Usually UAV image is an RGB compiosite provided as GeoTIFF of 16 or 8 "
"bit. The data type will be automatically converted to 8 bit on the side "
"of the Mapflow. Alternatively: use the `preprocessing script "
"<https://github.com/Geoalert/mapflow_data_preprocessor/>`_ for preparing "
"your image for Mapflow processing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:199 7b8ae67cf57541d58763f444a88687ba
msgid ""
"You can reduce the size of the image using GDAL translate. "
"(https://gdal.org/) E.g. using JPEG compression. ``gdal_translate -co "
"compress=JPEG input.tif output.tif`` By default the compression quality "
"is 75% (``gdal_translate -co compress=JPEG -co jpeg_quality=75 input.tif "
"output.tif``) but it doesn’t really impact the quality of the Mapflow "
"mask whenever the resolution of the input iage meets the recommended "
"params."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:204 084b649226ff4856a2b6b89aefb49cea
msgid "The same can be done using QGIS interface:"
msgstr "То же самое можно сделать через интерфейс QGIS:"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:212 cb65d393dea645acb8a19085814a653f
msgid ""
"Tell us if you have more tips to share with the community or if you have "
"more questions – we are ready to help."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:214 c4f8882d070f4341ad16596af33cd1e2
msgid "**Run the flow!**"
msgstr "**Запустите обработку!**"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:218 64bea5be56b94687add2c73ae36e457e
msgid "How to view results using Kepler.gl"
msgstr "Как просматривать результаты с помощью Kepler.gl"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:220 a499dd2bd26d45e1959bfc4c93a13d28
msgid ""
"**Kepler.gl** is an open source tool designed for geospatial data "
"analysis. It is a simple yet powerful for displaying and exploring "
"geodatasets."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:222 76160b9ae3b14cebb0004608ab647cae
msgid ""
"To view the processing results in the Mapflow, select the required "
"processing and press the button *\"Open in kepler.gl\"*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:225 1633008888d74e198f36e19308fdd3e6
msgid ""
"You can share your processing view in Kepler by copying the open URL "
"(right click on *\"Open in kepler.gl\"* --> Copy Link Address)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:227 7137d4f4262545de9f563e258ceac08f
msgid ""
"Using the Kepler you can change the visual properties of data, set "
"filters, and choose a background map."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:231 eada75bc3e0c4a4284023a6ab970e14b
msgid "Layers tab"
msgstr "Вкладка Layers"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:233 67c4a4d72887459db100fc92eb420a87
msgid ""
"Click on the layer name to bring up the *Layer settings* from the drop-"
"down menu. To hide all data, click on the *eye* icon."
msgstr ""

#: 1a54c6f6afed46b1b18f33205fafb99c
msgid "View layer settings"
msgstr "Настройки слоя"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:242 ee48aded4a5145fa88707cacbcafd0ef
msgid "These settings allow you to choose a more suitable type of received data:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:244 e4297840b30446a3b61f162d0b7a9d6e
msgid ""
"*Fill color.* You can choose any color from the palette for polygons, and"
" also hide the display of data by changing the position of the slider. "
"You can change the transparency of polygons (property *Opacity*) in the "
"additional settings of this function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:245 c04d051152004e25bcf4512781452a77
msgid ""
"*Stroke color.* You can choose any color from the palette for outlining "
"polygons, as well as completely remove the stroke. You can change the "
"transparency of the stroke (property *Opacity*) In the additional "
"settings of this function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:246 b86c0d17cbf747cda09e1d32e8c7dc62
msgid "*Stroke width.* Controls the thickness of the stroke."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:247 b0910e45559b4d40a10e140a597898b7
msgid ""
"*Height.* Allows you to view data with heights in 3D format. Set the "
"desired coefficient and select the attribute of the layer with heights."
msgstr ""

#: c53db8ef8b3544b58c73ad2afcef3b55
msgid "3D buildings"
msgstr "Здания в 3D"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:257 6320f1d455434c7899256309c06f7184
msgid "Filters tab"
msgstr "Вкладка Filters"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:259 32e6fa58e07a4566ba124f192f61b3f4
msgid ""
"This tab allows you to add a filter of interest by a specific attribute "
"of the layer (as in this case, the filter is set by classes with "
"different typology of buildings)."
msgstr ""

#: b87a6547c00e49e18699a889d3db0b65
msgid "Filter panel"
msgstr "Панель фильтров"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:269 53992c253b984b6d90333e5db2c4fb60
msgid "Interaction tab"
msgstr "Вкладка Interaction"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:271 8f7d64f3870141428a86c51b2a6d3921
msgid ""
"You can select or remove attributes that will be visible in the menu that"
" appears when you hover over an object. It is also possible to turn on "
"the panel indicating longitude and latitude."
msgstr ""

#: 5232fc49eb4f452ea903d89622c85735
msgid "Interaction panel"
msgstr "Панель взаимодействия"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:282 dd4ed878cc3149b0b19c143a52667598
msgid "Base map tab"
msgstr "Вкладка Base map"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:284 5d56ed3d7d5f4ec49a041beb7ab00669
msgid ""
"Here you can choose the styles of the map, as well as choose to display "
"its various layers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:288 a5989ece0f934f14babaa70ff651b3dd
msgid "How to run Mapflow on external infrastructure"
msgstr "Как запустить Mapflow на внешней инфраструктуре"

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:290 fedb142d32cb4760a2817b7e74a2564f
msgid ""
"Currently, you have to contact us if you have a request to run Mapflow "
"(as a platform or as a separate imagery analysis workflows) on external "
"infrastructure. However, we partner with cloud integrators to conduct "
"projects for their clients."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/userguides/howto.rst:294 6e2d3fd2edf748428f6fb1dff58e5433
msgid "How to run Mapflow using Geocloud"
msgstr "Как запустить Mapflow с помощью Geocloud"

